<br>
The problem now is convincing the masses that we are indeed quite powerful and are a solid addition to a group. There's no easy way to do this,  and will likely just take time. It doesn't help that there's relatively few magicians compared to other classes, so it's not like many people have spent much, if any time with one. All my friends appreciate what a magician can do, and while I can't always get a group as soon as I'd like, if I am persistant, I usually can.<br>
<br>
My only gripe is I can't really solo terribly well while waiting to join a group. Sure, I could dump all my mana to kill one mob in PoD or PoN, but that's not very productive and frustrating. It doesn't bug me other classes can solo, it doesn't even bug me other classes can solo better than me, it does bug me that I cannot solo effectively (I do not consider one mob every 15 minutes to be effective).<br>
