<br>
Before PoP, there were too many classes that were about damage dealing.<br>
<br>
After PoP, there's EVEN MORE classes that are about damage dealing. Magicians, losing mod rod 2, used to do damage+mod rods, but now, do damage, putting them in the exact same category as wizards and rogues. Monks also have moved into this same category.<br>
<br>
Rangers, Rogues, Magicians, Beastlords, Wizards, Necromancers I think, Monks, Druids maybe, all have to compete for 2.5 spots in a group. Enchanters/Shamans compete for 1.5 spots in a group. Clerics compete for 1 spot in a group. Paladins, Shadowknights, and Warriors compete for 1, rarely 2 or more spots in a group.<br>
<br>
The problem is that there are WAY more classes competing for those 2-3 damage spots than there are competing for anything else. The next closest competition is Teh Tank Spot, which is almost as bad because most people tend to want a warrior instead of a pally or sk, whereas people are more torn on which damage class would be best for their group.<br>
<br>
EQ is in the saddest class balance shape it's been in for a while, because almost all the classes do the same thing, slightly different.<br>
<br>
It will only get worse, I suspect, as PoP weapons and such start to be more mainstreem, and people see which classes are really the best damagers (i.e. if rangers parsing 202 with 14/17 and 21/24 weapons &amp; nuking compare to monks parsing 155 with their weaker weapons.)<br>
<br>
And now, less classes have a fallback ability. Monks could no longer get a group if they did less damage, since they can't tank either. SOE isn't giving classes much 'other reason' to get groups. <p>Happy trails.</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=krilenspiritlink>Krilen Spiritlink</A> at: 11/16/02 7:40:15 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ylaine76>Ylaine76</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1147<br> <font color=#333333>(11/16/02 9:22:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7880.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mages...a dying class?</span><hr size=1> The problem is that virtually everyone sits LFG now, its not because you're a mage it's because there are too many people for too few groups /shrug<br>
